By Joy Kaka Abuja – The police on Tuesday arraigned two men in a Kubwa Grade 1 Area Court for allegedly assaulting one Moses Osor at an Automatic Teller Machine (ATM) gallery. The police charged  Joseph Okpara, 33, and a sales representative, Newton Maliki, 30, with joint act, assault and mischief. The Prosecutor, Babajide Olanipekun, told the court that Osor reported the matter at the Dutse Alhaji Police Station on April 15. He said while the complainant  on April 14, expressed his displeasure to the defendants who jumped the queue at an prosecutor also said that Maliki chased the complainant into the car park and he lost his “palm sandals” valued at N25, 000 got missing. He said the offence contravened the provisions of sections 79, 265 and 327 of the Penal Code. The defendants pleaded not guilty. The judge, Ibrahim Balarabe, admitted the defendants  to bail in the sum of N100, 000 each with one surety each who must reside within the court’s jurisdiction. Balarabe adjourned the case until May 20, for hearing.